  <bioghist id="aspace_410830aabef4c62a9f5463165319eaa9">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>In 1975, the club acquired a Victorian birdcage said to have been owned by Liberty Hyde Bailey. Over the years, the club annually auctioned off the cage; the winner enjoyed it for a year and then put it up for rebid. Proceeds went to the club's scholarship fund. Eventually the cage was given to Gertrude ("Red") H. Smith (Cornell Class of 1947), whose mother Mary Wright Harvey founded the club in 1934 and was its first president.</p>  </bioghist>
  <prefercite id="aspace_cfa6015e5c35b03f4a7669d0dac2f96a">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Cornell Women's Club of Batavia records, #41-6-3435. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_82cf069c413fb3c68c5b9f486cb86ea3">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Includes meeting minutes; newspaper clippings; correspondence; photographs of the Orleans County group dinners, 1987-1988; and a banner.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_e4a83a57cf042e072e48c5bde5230919">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Also, a Victorian bird cage and copies of letters and clippings about it.</p>  </scopecontent>
